column61: I would recommend Hack the Hood because the program and the people working with us are truly dedicated to engaging students into the technology world in a way that honors racial, gender, and economic justice. I also really appreciate how the racial backgrounds of the team of educators in Hack the Hood is reflective of a cohort of students who are BI+POC. That really mattered to me because in tech/high education spaces, these dialogues about colonialism/race/gender ~must~ be led by people who are impacted by these systems. I also loved the enthusiasm, community building, and overall support that I as a participant received.
